    "Perhaps after introducing several Goedel expansions, we will be able to understand a great part of our intelligence, but as the great Mathematician predicted in his incompleteness theorem, certainly not in full.",
    "In the next section we dive into the inner mechanisms of both AI and NI in hope of shedding more light to their modus operandi.",
    "Inner workings and mechanismsMany differences between AI and NI reside in their underlying structuring and operating procedures.",
    "Artificial intelligence operates mainly deterministically based on algorithms, and often based in statistical models that enable computer programs to perform tasks requiring human intelligence.",
    "These algorithms rely on computational power, big datasets which are used for machine learning, and several types of neural networks."
